caption: Went for a friend’s birthday and loved the service, the food was even better!!! 10/10 for me

The place is clean, cozy, dim. Decor is simple yet cultural. Menu is modest. Food is good. Presentation is admirable. Service is impeccable. Good location. Parking easy to find. Good for families, groups, singles or date. Lack one star because No alcohol beverages sold.

I live in the area and was so surprised to know that there is such a great Mexican food restaurant 10 minutes from my place. Everything is on point : 5 star 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 service, absolutely delicious VERY fresh beautifully decorated dishes. Guacamole and chips are the best we've ever tried. Guacamole was unbelievably creamy and to die for, mmmmm so yami 😋😋😋. My dish of choice was cactus taco 🌮 and they were so loaded and big for only $12 - can absolutely be shared, but they are soo good, it's hard to not eat them all 😍😍😍. This place is A TOP LEVEL. Lamps decoration is very cool - made of buckets 👍🏽. It's so rare to find this level of service in residential areas but this one makes me feel like in some upscale area of Manhattan or Park Slope or Williamsburg. I will be back for sure and will consider them for take out and delivery always! This restaurant exceeded our expectations on many levels. Great for dinners, lunch and even breakfast.

Feel bad giving them low stars since they just opened but I was disappointed . The staff was very nice but the food was not great. Burrito barely had any meat, we literally had to look for the meat to see if they put any, couldn’t taste it at all. Tacos were dry and came without any kind of sauce on the side. The soup for $8 was just broth with big pieces of mostly carrots and celery, ~5 pieces of potatoes and a whole chicken drum and thigh (don’t get me wrong, I love chicken and it’s a chicken soup after all, but I don't want to be taking out plain boiled chicken out of my soup to be able to eat it instead of just having it in pieces already where I can just enjoy it without worrying about breaking it up myself) . Some of the carrot pieces weren’t even peeled. I might give them another try in a month or two when they’re more established but for now I’ll be getting my tacos at the food truck on McDonald Avenue.
